    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated that Yahya bin Abu Ishaq Al-Hunai said:\n&ldquo;I asked Anas bin Malik: What if a man gives his brother a loan, then (the borrower) give him a gift? The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: If anyone of you borrow something then he gives (the lender) a gift or gives him a ride on his riding-beast, he should not accept the gift or the ride, unless they used to treat each other in that manner beforehand.&rdquo;',
