    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\n&ldquo;The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) ruled concerning a fetus that (the blood money) was a slave, male and female. The one against whom this verdict was passed said:  Should we pay blood money for one who neither ate, drunk, shouted, nor cried, (at the moment of birth)? One such as this should be overlooked . The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: This man speaks like a poet. (But the blood money for a fetus is) a slave, male, or female.&rdquo;',
