    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\n&ldquo;A man came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and said: &ldquo;O Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), tell me, which of the people has most right to my good companionship? He said: Yes, by your father, you will certainly be told. He said: Your mother, He said: Then who? He said: Then your mother. He said: Then who? He said: Then your mother. He said: Then who? He said: Then your father. He said: Tell me, O Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) about my wealth- how should I give in charity? He said: Yes, by Allah (SWT) you will certainly be told. You should give in charity when you are still healthy and greedy for wealth, hoping for a long life and fearing poverty. Do not tarry until your soul reaches here and you say: &ldquo;My wealth of for so-and-so,&rdquo; and &ldquo;My wealth of for so-and-so,&rdquo; and it will be for them even though you dislike that.&rdquo;',
