    hadithEnglish:
      'It was narrated that Asma bint Abi Bakr said:\n&ldquo;We went out with the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) in Ihram. The Prophet (ﷺ) said: Whoever has a sacrificial animal with him, let him remain in Ihram. Whoever does not have a sacrificial animal with him, let him exit Ihram. She said: I did not have a sacrificial animal with me, so I exited Ihram, but Zubair had a sacrificial animal with him, so he did not exit Ihram. So I put on my regular clothes and came to Zubair, and he said: Go away from me. I said: Are you afraid I am going to jump on you?!&rdquo;',
